-- Reed Elsevier sticks to positive outlook
-- By Paul Sandle
-- Thu Oct 23, 2014 02:15AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 23 (Reuters) - Anglo Dutch Reed Elsevier <REL.L> <ELSN.AS> said a 4 percent rise in underlying revenue in the first nine months kept it on track to meet its goal of growing revenue and profit this year.

The professional information provider posted strongest growth in its risk and business information and exhibitions units on Thursday, up 7 percent and 8 percent respectively.